chunk_content: Screening for TB and/or initiation of anti-TB therapy might not happen at the same time that ART is started. For PLHIV new to HIV care, those who are diagnosed with TB are usually started on anti-TB therapy before they initiate ART (e.g., 2-8 weeks as per current recommendations). Regardless of when they occur relative to ART initiation, TB screening and initiation of TB therapy should be included for all patients who were already on ART or who started ART at any time during the reporting period. For TB screening type, patients who receive CXR or mWRD for screening purposes (i.e., as an initial approach for identifying presumptive TB) should be reported under the corresponding disaggregates ‘CXR’ or ‘mWRD’, even if they were screened using algorithms that also include symptom screening.
